From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 14:33:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 42/42] web-app: relay picker on instant onboarding from the
 live chatmail directory
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The "create profile" onboarding screen always signed up on one fixed
relay (the SLOTHFUL_DEFAULT_CHATMAIL one, or upstream's default
instance). Give users a choice: a dropdown right above the
privacy-policy consent, listing the default relay first and then the
public relays from the chatmail directory.

- relayDirectory.ts fetches the directory live from the chatmail pages
  sources (relays.markdown behind https://chatmail.at/relays), and
  keeps only relays whose hostname the WS→TCP bridge's /dns endpoint
  resolves to at least one IP — a relay the bridge can't resolve can't
  be signed up on from this app. The bridge URL is resolved exactly
  like the runtime does (?proxy= > saved > instance default >
  localhost). The default relay is never probed away and always listed
  first. Successful loads are cached per page load; failures retry.
- relayDirectoryParse.ts is the tolerant markdown scanner (the file is
  hand-maintained prose, not a machine format): it accepts a hostname
  only where the author spelled it out — dcaccount: signup targets,
  self-named links like [nine.testrun.org](https://nine.testrun.org),
  and bare autolinks — so decorative links and prose domains stay out.
  Unit-tested in src/tests/relayDirectory.test.ts.
- RelayPicker.tsx renders the dropdown (a DeltaSelect, matching the
  display-name input above it) only when there is a real choice: more
  than one relay, and no scanned dcaccount:/dclogin: QR pinning the
  server. Everything fails soft to "no dropdown".
- The choice lives in InstantOnboardingContext so account creation
  (useInstantOnboarding builds dcaccount:<picked host>) and the consent
  text (UserAgreement links the picked relay's /privacy.html) always
  agree; resetInstantOnboarding clears it. A scanned account/login QR
  still overrides everything, as before.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
